  "curation": {
    "synopsis": "Word has reached the Sabbat Worlds that the Saint herself — six thousand years dead — has been reincarnated on the pious but unimportant world of Herodor, in the Civitas Beati. The Ghosts are pulled there for sainthood-guard duty, and Gaunt arrives to find that the reincarnated Saint is Sanian — the young Hagian priestess from Honour Guard — manipulated into the role by the careerist Lord General Lugo as a tool for his own advancement. The fates conspire faster than Lugo can: the Chaos warmaster Enok Innokenti, recognising the propaganda threat, dispatches nine specialised assassins (one per Holy Wound that originally ended Sabbat's life) at the head of a Blood Pact army to kill the Saint before she can take the stage. The novel pivots from political intrigue to a Civitas-Beati siege, ending Saint-tetralogy with a real-or-fake-saint reveal that lands on real — and that real saint dies, taking Innokenti with her, before the Crusade can fully capitalise. Series turning point.",
